result.execSummary:
The defendant Jonathan Scott Debauch was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Posses w/Intent-Fentanyl (<=10g), a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(dm)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

BAIL HEARING - 
Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crime of possess fentanyl with intent to deliver and possess drug paraphernalia.  The matter is continued for initial appearance on 07-18-22 at 1:30 pm.  Bail is set at $750.00 cash bond with the conditions that defendant must maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol and drugs except for prescribed medications taken in prescribed doses and defendant is not to possess any controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.  Bail not furnished and defendant is remanded to the custody of the Sheriff.
